arch a_townsman
name Valdoran Tourism Advisor
msg
@match brave adventurer
I saw it immediately, I have a keen eye for such things!

@match Valdoran Tourism Bureau|bureau
The Valdoran City Council (under command of our blessed King) decided
to foster travel to our nice city.

To this end, many facilities especially for the beginning adventurer were built in our city. Unlike Scorn,
we have quite a variety of low- and medium-level training maps and dungeons - and more are in the planning stage.

Although Valdor is quite near to Scorn, it can be hard to find, which is why additionally this Tourism Bureau was built, which
offers cheap and convinient travel between Scorn and Valdor (with some travel restrictions).

@match travel restrictions
Uhm... now that you ask, there really are no I<restrictions> - you can travel freely within the city, but access to the outside areas of Valdor
are limited to those with visiting passes.

@match visiting passes|passes|pass
Those passes are currently only issued at the border. We are working to lift this restriction, but bureaucracy is the same everywhere, isn't it?

<laughs nervously>

@match Scorn
You are in Scorn now, if you were confused.

@match Valdor
Valdor is a small but very important City State, north-east of Scorn. Originally a small mining town, we are now well known
for our training areas.

@match travel|vacation
Ah, yes, I like your direct way of getting to the point quickly. We didn't spare any expenses to make
quick and affordable travel a reality. Due to the technical difficulties with dragon transport, we employ the help
of first-class sorcerers to quickly bring you to Valdor, and back again.

Just go and talk to the sorcerer-of-the-day in the back.

@match hi
Hello, brave adventurer! My name is Dabor Belanbor from the Valdoran Tourism Bureau.

Is it possible that I could spark your interest in a short and very affordable vacation to the
splendid city of Valdor?

@match *
I am sorry, Sir, but I can only help you with tourism-related questions.
endmsg
